body_html:
@sokunmin Did you try on Mac for the first time today or you tried last Friday as well?

The demo app configured below
compile 'org.tensorflow:tensorflow-lite:+'
1st step Android Studio does is downloading
https://google.bintray.com/tensorflow/org/tensorflow/tensorflow-lite/maven-metadata.xml
which tells you what's the latest version.

And we once had a broken 0.1.8-rc1 published.

If you don't clear the project / gradle local cache, it will stick with 0.1.8-rc1 without re-consulting maven-metadata.xml (which is fixed now w/ all 0.1.8-rc* removed).

You can try deleting ~/.gradle/caches on Mac OS and clean / rebuild your Android project.
